  {
    "client_msg_id": "2595a752-33a0-46c3-97ed-c5cdb3a93f6c",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "though the risk of a noodl-y mess is very very real, I'd say that the node/wire handshake is direct perception of data &amp; action flow\n\nthe connectors remove the cognitive load of keeping track of what effects what in 2D space -- so my inclination would be to draw them always\n\nalso, if a user draws some but not others, that inconsistency is even more cognitive load, where the legibility of the graph now depends on a previous builder (or even yourself 2 months ago!) making the right choices in terms of which connector to manifest",
    "user": "U023V63MF6V",
    "ts": "1679527265.334899",
